TY  - JOUR
AU  - Bo, Hong
AU  - Lensink, Robert
AU  - Sterken, Elmer
T1  - Uncertainty and Financing Constraints
PY  - 2003
Y1  - 2003/01/01
DO  - 10.1023/A:1024570312059
JO  - Review of Finance
JA  - Rev Financ
VL  - 7
IS  - 2
SP  - 297
EP  - 321
SN  - 1572-3097
AB  - Using a panel of Dutch listed firms this paper provides empirical evidence for the hypothesis that more risky firms are confronted with more severe capital market constraints than relatively less risky firms. The paper also contributes to the discussion on the usefulness of cash flow as a measure of financial constraints. We present a stochastic version of the Kaplan-Zingales (1997) model. We show that cash flow sensitivity can be used as a meaningful indicator of financing constraints if firms are classified by the degree of uncertainty they face and if the uncertainty originates from cost uncertainty. JEL classification codes: E22, G32.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1023/A:1024570312059
ER  - 



